29/05/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The National Security Council (MGK) convened Wednesday (28 May) to discuss EU affairs, Iraq-related issues and the dispute over Cyprus. 
With regard to EU accession reforms, the military expressed reservations about some articles in proposed legal measures. 
The MGK, composed of both government and military officials, will hold a special meeting next month to further discuss EU-related issues. 
(Hurriyet, Milliyet - 29/05/03; Anadolu Agency, NTV - 28/05/03)
